    <header class="article-header pt-3 pb-8" id="article-top">
      <h1 title="Low or no output level in Reference 4 Systemwide [MAC]" class="text-3xl font-medium leading-tight">
        Low or no output level in Reference 4 Systemwide [MAC]
        
      </h1>

      <div class="article-author pt-4">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="avatar article-avatar">
            
            <img src="https://support.sonarworks.com/system/photos/145169469/10250333_10203084930398565_370185915020170676_n.jpg" alt="Avatar" class="user-avatar h-16 rounded-full" />
          </div>
          <div class="article-meta pl-3 pb-1">
            
              Matīss
              <a class="article-subscribe" title="Opens a sign-in dialog" rel="nofollow" role="button" data-auth-action="signin" aria-selected="false" href="/hc/en-us/articles/115004132034-Low-or-no-output-level-in-Reference-4-Systemwide-MAC-/subscription.html">Follow</a>
            <div class="article-updated meta-data text-regular text-sm">Updated <time datetime="2022-02-14T19:44:42Z" title="2022-02-14T19:44:42Z" data-datetime="relative">February 14, 2022 19:44</time></div>
          </div>
        </div> 
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="article-info">
      <div class="article-content">
        <main class="article article-body text-justify">
          <p>If you encounter a situation where Systemwide is receiving seemingly low or no input signal at all, it's worth checking the following settings:</p>
<p>In Spotlight search, type "Audio MIDI Setup", open it and click on Sonarworks Systemwide device. There make sure that all three volume faders are maxed out (see the image below)</p>
<p>      <img src="/hc/article_attachments/360036090153/mceclip0.png" alt="mceclip0.png" width="563" height="375" /></p>
<p>If you are still not getting any signal from Systemwide, please make sure that Systemwide isn't muted in your Mac System Preferences &gt; Sound settings Output tab (image below) </p>
<p><img src="/hc/article_attachments/360037023353/Screenshot_2019-05-29_at_11.29.40.png" alt="Screenshot_2019-05-29_at_11.29.40.png" width="609" height="476" /></p>
<p>If you are on MacOS 10.14 Mojave, please also make sure that you have allowed the microphone access to Sonarworks software. You can <a href="/hc/en-us/articles/360010481074-Mojave-requires-microphone-access-for-Systemwide" target="_self">read more about it here</a>. </p>
        </main>

        <div class="article-attachments">
          <ul class="attachments">
        
            
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

