                  </div>
                  <div class="comment-meta">
                    <span title="Kārlis Stenders">
                      
                        Kārlis Stenders
                      
                    </span>

                    <span class="comment-published">
                      <time datetime="2019-04-08T07:30:20Z" title="2019-04-08T07:30:20Z" data-datetime="calendar">April 08, 2019 07:30</time>
                      
                    </span>
                  </div>

                  

                  
                </div>

                <section class="comment-body font-light"><p>It's not the mic level, but the Systemwide device level you're adjusting (just like any other hardware or virtual device in Audio MIDI Setup).</p>
<p>If you're referring to the 'Allow Mic Access' in Security &amp; Privacy Preferences - that seems to be an issue with most audio production software on MacOS. We're not exactly sure why it is mic access particularly, but it seems to be the way Mac handles creating a virtual device - you will see the same issue when installing other audio software too. Thanks!</p></section>
              </div>

